snippet.title: AVENGERS: DOOMSDAY (2026) | Fantastic 4 & Wakandans Trailer | Marvel Comics | Concept
snippet.description:
#Marvel #Avengers #Avengersdoomsday #ChrisEvans #Robertdowneyjr
 
🎥 Attention viewers! (ITS FAN MADE)
The Avengers: Doomsday Trailer unleashes the most dangerous chapter of the Marvel Cinematic Universe as the Avengers face total annihilation in Avengers Doomsday (2026). With Robert Downey Jr. rumored as Doctor Doom, the Doomsday trailer teases multiversal chaos, Wakanda under siege, shocking leaks, and the possible arrival of the X-Men and Fantastic Four as the MCU enters Phase 6. From intense Wakanda sequences and Doctor Doom’s rise to world-ending stakes, this Avengers Doomsday Marvel trailer sets up an epic collision of heroes, villains, and destinies that will redefine the future of Marvel Studios.

The inspiration behind this video:
The internet is breaking again with the latest Avengers Doomsday trailer leak! In this video, we break down the shocking footage from the Doomsday trailer 4, also known as the Doomsday Wakanda trailer. This specific Doomsday teaser reveals an unexpected alliance between Wakanda and the Fantastic Four, opening with a chilling monologue from Shuri about preparing her people for the "afterlife." We analyze every frame of this wakanda doomsday trailer leaked footage, specifically the scene where Namor joins the fight and the hilarious first interaction where M'Baku meets The Thing. This Doomsday Fantastic Four teaser moment confirms that the multiverse is collapsing, bringing these heroes together to face the ultimate threat.

We connect this new wakanda trailer leak to the previous Doomsday X Men trailer, which featured Cyclops and Magneto making their final stand. As Marvel Studios ramps up marketing for Avengers 2026, it is clear that Robert Downey Jr Doctor Doom is waging war on every corner of the multiverse simultaneously. We discuss how these isolated Doomsday leak clips paint a terrifying picture of the Doctor Doom MCU variant. Is this truly a Doctor Doom movie where the villain wins, forcing the surviving Wakandans and Mutants to retreat into a Secret Wars scenario?

Finally, we look ahead to the full Avengers Doomsday official trailer release and what to expect from Marvel Phase 6. We theorize on why Marvel is attaching these specific Doomsday trailer spots to Avatar: Fire and Ash and whether the official Avengers Doomsday marvel trailer will finally show RDJ in the full armor facing off against the new team. From the doomsday wakanda teaser leak details to the full Avengers Doomsday cast breakdown, this is your ultimate guide to the end of the Marvel Cinematic Universe and the rise of Avengers Doctor Doom.

snippet.title: Man City SMASH Exeter to progress! 💥 | Manchester City  (10-1) Exeter | Emirates FA Cup 2025-26
snippet.description:
Last year's finalists Man City put ten past Exeter to progress to the Fourth Round of the Emirates FA Cup. Max Alleyne opened the scoring with his first for Manchester City, before a goal from Rodri and two own goals sent City into the break with a four goal lead. Debutant Antoine Semenyo found the net in  the second half, as well as a brace from Rico Lewis and goals from Tijani Reijnders, Nico O'Reilly and Ryan McAidoo capped off the win. Exeter netted a consolation goal late on from the boot of George Birch, but it was plain sailing for City in the end.

snippet.title: "Battle Hymn of the Empire" - Marsh Family adaptation of "Battle Hymn of the Republic" about Trump
snippet.description:
The “Battle Hymn of the Republic” is an iconic American song, drawing on lots of roots and precursors, but pulled into its most famous shape by abolitionist Julia Ward Howe. During the American Civil War it became a signature marching song for the Union Army, linked to patriotism and faith, and has since become part of the canon of American national music. We do not attempt or treat it lightly, but our version reflects on how the first week of 2026 has already seen Trump's troops advancing his domestic and foreign policy agendas. Every marching step is another step away from the principles and traditions embedded in the song: we have seen the transgression of international law in Venezuela, the murder of unarmed Americans in Minneapolis (and its defence by the administration), the US's withdrawal from multiple international organisations, and explicit threats issued to other sovereign powers and polities, including Greenland. 

___________________________

- https://open.spotify.com/artist/6AYmbCwi92V29y69lkRkRa 

___________________________ 

LYRICS:

Our eyes have seen the stories of the breaking of the laws
Of the trampling and the wreckage, of the use of deadly force
Those who loosed the hate and violence now expect to reap rewards
Trump’s troops go marching on

We have seen it in the barbed-wire of his dark detention camps
His unbuilding of the White House and his grifting and his scams
In his sick self-righteous sentences and postures with his hands
Trump’s hatred marches on

How he longs to have an empire
How he longs to have an empire
How he hankers for an empire!
Trump’s troops are marching on.

ICE shot dead an unarmed mother sitting harmless at the wheel
They might spin it to condemn her, but the footage shows what’s real
Yet they fear no retribution for the murder they conceal
Since Trump is marching on

He has Delta Force to mobilise with choppers and a fleet
He’ll be stripping nations’ assets, with aggression and deceit
Oh, beware if you’ve got min-er-als or dare to drag your feet!
For Trump is marching on

How he longs to have an empire
How he longs to have an empire
How he hankers for an empire!
Trump’s troops are marching on.

In the reckless opportunities Trump seeks across the seas
He gives license to the tyrants – to the Putins, and the Xis
They all lie about their motives, and the prize is never peace
While Trump is marching on

He is drumming out the glory of a land once free and brave
He is chiselling the marble but the statue looks depraved
Now the world must watch this ghoul, as he launches tidal waves
Let’s hope one day they’re gone

Glory, glory, Hallelujah!
Glory, glory, Hallelujah!
Glory, glory, Hallelujah!
Let’s hope one day they’re gone

snippet.title: Avengers: Doomsday - Trailer 4 "The Wakandans & The Fantastic 4 Will Return" (Concept)
snippet.description:
— Attention Viewers ⚠️
— This is a Fan-Made Concept Trailer for:
— Avengers: Doomsday - The Wakandans & The Fantastic 4 Will Return

— This video is a fan-made concept trailer, created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes.The goal behind this trailer is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through a concept trailer based on a unique and original idea. By combining various effects, sound design, and AI technologies, I’ve crafted a cinematic experience that reimagines familiar worlds in bold and imaginative ways. This trailer is not official and is intended to entertain, inspire, and engage with the YouTube community. Thank you for your support — now let’s dive into a world shaped by creativity and craft. 🎬✨

— In this concept trailer for Avengers: Doomsday, the story turns inward, exploring the quiet consequences of legacy, leadership, and choices made long after victory. Shuri, carrying the weight of loss and responsibility as Wakanda’s protector, seeks purpose beyond mourning, confronting the reality that kings and nations must prepare not only for death, but for what follows it. Her path draws Wakanda into uneasy alignment with Talokan and toward an unprecedented meeting with the Fantastic Four, where old worlds and new ideals collide in a moment decades in the making. As alliances form through restraint rather than force, a darker intelligence emerges in the shadows—one that does not mourn the past or protect the present, but claims ownership of the future itself. With Doctor Doom positioning himself beyond kings, heroes, and afterlives, the film sets the stage for a conflict rooted not in spectacle, but in ideology, inevitability, and the cost of surviving history.

The skies are calling and this time Maverick faces a mission that'll push him beyond any limits he's ever known. This concept trailer brings Tom Cruise back as Captain Pete Mitchell alongside Denzel Washington as a legendary admiral with his own complicated history in the danger zone. When a new global threat demands the impossible from the Navy's best, these two warriors must bridge generations and egos to train a new squad for aerial combat that makes their previous missions look like training exercises. Afterburners ignite at Mach speed, missiles lock onto ghosts, and somewhere between glory and sacrifice lies the ultimate question of whether some pilots are born to fly or born to fall.

Bruno Mars is a 16x GRAMMY®-winning global superstar, singer, songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, producer, and one of the most-streamed artists in the world. Known for his showmanship and chart-toppers, Bruno has set a number of records throughout his career, including becoming the first artist ever to hit 150 million monthly listeners on Spotify, appearing on two of the fastest songs to reach one billion streams (for “Die with a Smile” with Lady Gaga and “APT.” with ROSÉ, and achieving the highest-certified song in RIAA history with 2010’s “Just the Way You Are”). Since launching a string of hits beginning in 2009, Bruno has sold over 150 million records worldwide, making him one of the best-selling artists of all time. Beyond his work as a soloist, Bruno is a member of the duo Silk Sonic with Anderson .Paak. In addition to his 35 Billboard Hot 100 hits, including nine number one singles, Bruno is the recipient of 16 GRAMMY® Awards (including “Album of the Year” for 24K Magic), 14 American Music Awards, and seven MTV Video Music Awards. His 24K Magic World Tour was among the highest-grossing tours in history, and within the top ten highest-grossing of the 2010s.
